Debug Pods running (or crashing) on a Node.
Pod should already be scheduled and running. Pod is not yet running, start with Debugging Pods.
The advanced debugging steps you need to know on which Node the Pod is running and have shell access to run commands on that Node.

[create a Deployment]
$ kubectl apply -f Deployment.yaml
$ kubectl apply -f https://k8s.io/examples/application/nginx-with-request.yaml

[check pod status]
$ kubectl get pods
NAME                                READY   STATUS    RESTARTS   AGE
nginx-deployment-67d4bdd6f5-cx2nz   1/1     Running   0          13s
nginx-deployment-67d4bdd6f5-w6kd7   1/1     Running   0          13s

[retrieve a lot more information about each of these pods]
$ kubectl describe pod nginx-deployment-67d4bdd6f5-w6kd7
Name:         nginx-deployment-67d4bdd6f5-w6kd7
